Series IV. Architecture & New York City-related Exhibitions
Marilyn Symmes collection of art exhibition ephemera
Marilyn Symmes collection of art exhibition ephemera

Includes material from architectural and New York City related shows and programs at the following museums, spaces, and galleries: Alliance for Downtown New York, Inc., Architectural League of New York, Architekturzentrum Wien, Arquitectonica: The Times Square Project, Brasserie Americaine, Franklin D. Roosevelt Four Freedoms Park, International Print Center New York, The Jewish Museum, Keith De Lellis Gallery, Kitchen Club, Max Protetch, and The Museum of Contemporary Art, Los Angeles. Also includes a pamphlet from The Jewish Museum that features questions and answers from the designers, Stefan Sagmeister and Jessica Walsh, on their exhibition, "Six Things", and includes a brief biography. Also includes a brochure from MOCA at the Geffen Contemporary on its exhibition, "At the End of the Century: 100 Years of Architecture" with an insert on another exhibition, "The Unbuilt".
